# ===================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ===================================
# This .gitignore protects:
# 1. Environment variables and configuration files
# 2. Database files containing user data
# 3. SSL certificates and private keys
# 4. Authentication tokens and API keys
# 5. Log files that may contain sensitive information
# 6. Backup files and database dumps
# 7. Development and testing artifacts
#
# IMPORTANT SECURITY PRACTICES:
# - Always use environment variables for secrets
# - Never hardcode API keys or passwords in code
# - Review files before committing with 'git status'
# - Use 'git-secrets' tool for additional protection
# - Regularly audit repository for accidentally committed secrets